  "prompt": "How do I get admissions in IIT's for ME?",
  "response": "To get admission to IITs for ME (Master of Engineering), follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- Bachelor's degree in Engineering/Technology\n- Minimum 60% aggregate marks\n- Valid GATE score (recommended)\n\n2. Entrance Exams:\n- GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering) is the primary entrance exam\n- Some IITs also conduct their own entrance tests\n\n3. Admission Process:\n- Apply through GATE counseling (JAM)\n- Register on the Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) website\n- Fill choices of IITs and courses\n- Participate in counseling rounds\n\n4. Selection Criteria:\n- GATE score\n- Academic performance\n- Category-wise seat reservation\n- Interview performance (for some programs)\n\n5. Required Documents:\n- GATE scorecard\n- Academic mark sheets\n- Graduation certificate\n- Category certificate (if applicable)\n- Identity proof\n- Passport-sized photographs\n\n6. Important Tips:\n- Start preparing for GATE early\n- Choose your specialization carefully\n- Research different IIT programs\n- Maintain a good academic record\n\nRecommended websites:\n- www.josaa.nic.in\n- www.gate.iitk.ac.in",
